docs.text: the most popular trend of the last couple of years has been the twist ending .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: watching one of these movies , everything seems to make sense until suddenly you are blown away by an unexpected surprise .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when the film ends , there is a moment of confusion , then recollection , then some more confusion , then possibly a second viewing for clarification .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this is a description of an ideal twist that perfects everything it sets out to do and more .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: good surprises make movies fun to watch .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: then there are the bad twists .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: you either know what is going to happen ten minutes into the movie ( i'm talking about you reindeer games ) or you did not guess the ending because it is so outrageously stupid .

docs.text: screwed perfectly suits the latter description .

docs.text: screwed is an inane christmas carol gone berserk with few genuine laughs and many acting embarrassments .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: norm macdonald stars as willard filmore , a hard working chauffeur who just wants a little respect from his rich , old , insidious boss , miss crock ( elaine stritch ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when he overhears her plans to fire him on christmas day , willard is convinced by his best friend rusty ( dave chapelle ) to kidnap crock's beloved dog and hold it for a ransom of one million dollars .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: too excited to pay any attention , the hapless losers' plan goes awry when the dog escapes and returns home .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: now crock thinks willard has been kidnapped and the two friends , realizing they can make even more money , decide to stage the fake kidnapping .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: of course , everything that could go wrong does .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the first forty-five minutes of screwed is harmless entertainment - a guilty pleasure that should be enjoyably bad .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but the convoluted script eventually builds into a disaster that is impossible to bear .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the more idiotic these characters get , the more reckless the script becomes .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: at one point , i wanted to get out of my seat and yell at these characters : " no , you idiot ! "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i'm not just talking about willard and rusty , who were extremely annoying , i'm also talking about the cops in this film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a monkey could have solved this case within an hour but these guys ( headed by murder one's daniel benzali ) were just too clueless to forgive .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they give real cops bad names .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: also poor danny devito apparently does not know how to turn down a role these days .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: looking almost identical to his penguin in batman : returns , every time he appeared on the screen i had to shake my head in disbelief .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he just didn't belong in this movie .

docs.text: macdonald and chapelle are veterans at these kinds of movies but devito made the film much worse than it already was , gross out humor is certainly not his forte .

docs.text: if you're a fan of norm macdonald's other chaotic comedy , dirty work , you might actually love this near-sequel .
